<br>
Additionally, when you are new to a raid area, or raid environment, understand that if you think we are being a bit harsh or loud in guildchat to get what needs to be done accomplished, we arent mad at you directly.  A lot of feelings can be hurt if you are sensitive enough, but it honestly isnt personal - it's VERY hard to get 45 people do do what you need them to do, to avoid breaking mez, to heal the right person, to listen up for loot, etc.  So if you do get your feelings hurt, as the raid leader or the person who upset you in tells after the raid, or maybe during a med break.  Chances are 200 to 1 that no one was mad at you, and we will really feel bad if we upset you.<br>
<br>
If we are in a new area and I'm on the raid, please always feel free to ask me about the area or maybe some hints.  One of the benefits of having played so long, is likely I've been there....and I'm always willing to help :)))<br>
